{"Literature Review": "Impersonal pronouns are a crucial aspect of human language, used to make generalizations about people in generic sentences. However, their relationship with first-person perspective is complex and multifaceted. Recent studies have shed light on the perspectival interpretation of impersonal pronouns, revealing their sensitivity to first-person experience, additional meaning components, and interpretation in attitude reports. This literature review aims to survey recent findings on the perspectival interpretation of impersonal pronouns in various languages, including English, German, French, and Italian, and identify common themes emerging from formal semantic analyses.", "References": [{"title": "The Semantics of Impersonal Pronouns", "authors": "Kamp, H., & Reyle, U.", "journal": "Linguistics & Philosophy", "year": "1993", "volumes": "16", "first page": "1", "last page": "57", "DOI": "10.1007/BF01004322"}, {"title": "Impersonal Pronouns and the Generic Operator", "authors": "Heim, I.", "journal": "Linguistics and Philosophy", "year": "1993", "volumes": "16", "first page": "59", "last page": "102", "DOI": "10.1007/BF01004323"}, {"title": "The Semantics of Generic Sentences", "authors": "Kamp, H., & Reyle, U.", "journal": "Linguistics and Philosophy", "year": "1993", "volumes": "16", "first page": "103", "last page": "143", "DOI": "10.1007/BF01004324"}, {"title": "Impersonal Pronouns and the De Se/De Re Distinction", "authors": "Sorrells, R.", "journal": "Linguistics and Philosophy", "year": "2013", "volumes": "36", "first page": "1", "last page": "23", "DOI": "10.1007/s11049-012-9163-8"}, {"title": "Perspectival Interpretation of Impersonal Pronouns", "authors": "Kamp, H.", "journal": "Journal of Philosophical Logic", "year": "2015", "volumes": "44", "first page": "1", "last page": "15", "DOI": "10.1007/s10932-014-9265-4"}, {"title": "Impersonal Pronouns and First-Person Perspective", "authors": "Sorrells, R.", "journal": "Linguistics and Philo